sub_title: Arts and Social Entrepreneur, Charity Fundraiser, Lecturer.
summary:
My career in the charity, arts and culture sector in the UK, Singapore and now Netherlands focuses on lecturing and professional development, community building, social enterprise, art start-up, marketing, events, audience development and fundraising. I volunteer on a variety of youth related projects, specialising in the arts and social enterprise. Most recently volunteering at UWC Maastricht as a facilitator for the IB Diploma students YSE Week 2023, and as a fundraiser with the Advancement Team for UWC scholarships. Past roles include lecturer of Arts Entrepreneurship and Strategic Thinking at Lasalle College of Arts (in 2023 Singapore University of the Arts); I founded Nuwa Pte Ltd in 2017; UK online eco store Pure Design in 2007; and served as Company Secretary and Business Manager to UK registered charity The Making in 2004-2007. 

[Credit to those in my profile picture - Cambodia Living Arts all female drumming troupe. Cambodia's only female drumming troupe. Performing at Bambu Stage in Siem Reap.]
